  "texts": [
    "According to HEC, this person offloads the cognitive work of remembering the numbers and following the division algorithm onto the paper by way of a culturally mediated practice of externalising the algorithm's steps (Hutchins, 2014; Vold & Schlimm, 2020).",
    "In a similar vein, we might think yet more of this cognitive work can be offloaded to a pocket calculator or a smartphone's calculator app.",
    "We might also think that AI assistants like ChatGPT offer even further ranging opportunities to offload cognition (I'll return to these putative examples in §5.4).",
    "In recent years, cognitive offloading has been the focus of empirical study (for reviews, see Risko & Gilbert, 2016; Armitage et al., 2020).",
    "This literature has been taken up by HEC's supporters since it provides a body of evidence that this kind of dependence on environmental and bodily resources is pervasive in and transformative of human cognition."
  ],
